    <section id="thila-homam" class="py-5">
      <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-center"><i class="bi bi-fire me-2"></i>Thila
          Homam</h2>
        <p class="text-center mb-5 text-muted">Know the significance, benefits,
          and process of Thila Homam at Rameswaram.</p>

        <!-- Why is Thila Homam performed? -->
        <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Why is Thila Homam Performed in
              Rameswaram?</h4>
            <p class="card-text">
              Rameswaram is considered one of the most sacred places to perform
              Thila Homam. It is one of the 12 Jyotirlingas and holds immense
              spiritual power. Performing the ritual here offers strong relief
              from <strong>Pitru Dosha</strong> by appeasing one's ancestors.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Sudden death in family with no reason</li>
              <li>Trouble in married life</li>
              <li>Delay in property settlements or legal issues</li>
              <li>Unexplained financial loss or job delays</li>
              <li>Lack of peace or frequent conflicts in the family</li>
              <li>Delay in childbirth</li>
              <li>Brings peace to ancestral souls</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- When should I perform? -->
        <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">When Should I Perform Thila Homam?</h4>
            <p class="card-text">
              Thila Homam can be performed on <strong>any day in
                Rameswaram</strong>. However, it is especially powerful on
              <strong>Amavasya (New Moon Day)</strong>. The duration depends on
              chant count, typically lasting <strong>around 3 hours</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Poojas Table -->
        <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm  border-0">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title mb-3">Other Important Poojas in
              Rameswaram</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Sudarshana Homam</li>
              <li>Sarpa Shanthi / Rahu Ketu Shanthi</li>
              <li>Naga Prathista (with idol)</li>
              <li>Kalathra Dosham / Swayamvara Parvathi Pooja</li>
              <li>Thithi / Sraddam / Divasam (Yearly ceremony)</li>
              <li>Hiranya Sradham</li>
              <li>Ganga Pooja with Rudra Paarayanam</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Dress code & Instructions -->
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Important Guidelines</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Dress Code:</strong> Men should wear dhoti. Women
                should wear saree or salwar.</li>
              <li><strong>Main Ingredient:</strong> Sesame seeds (Til or Ellu)
                are used in the ritual.</li>
              <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Approx. 3 hours (depends on chant
                count).</li>
              <li><strong>Cost:</strong> Depends on chant count; higher for
                Brahmins due to additional procedures.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

